gomodel:SYNGO_5285  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6a,b: immunofluorescence imaging of cultured hippocampal neurons showed overexpressed α-myosin IIb (MYH10) was localized to the base of the spine head, showing enrichment in spines vs. dendrites.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Briefly, the hippocampi of embryonal day 17 Wistar rat fetuses of either sex were dissected and brains obtained.\"\n\n\"mCherry-tagged SWAP-70, myosin IXb, and myosin IIb constructs were kind gifts from Martin Bähler (SWAP-70 and Myosin IXb, WestfalianWilhelms-University, Münster, Germany) and Alan Rick Horwitz (MHCIIb, University of Virginia, USA).\"\n\nHuman protein was overexpressed, also for mutated sequence (Figure 5)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5285" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

